item.title: Help, teleporting!
item.dc:creator: @Telenim Telenim
item.description:
@Telenim wrote:

The best way I could think of for finding the teleport locations for things that teleport you to random squares is what Fox0wnage said. Look in the cmd box for the action button ID and search for it, change the coords, and you’re done.

item.title: Help, teleporting!
item.dc:creator: @Fox0wnage Fox0wnage
item.description:
@Fox0wnage wrote:

First things first…you need to check your coordinates when you teleport and search for the coordinates in the clickingmost.java.
Or check your server command prompt and when you click the teleport button, it should tell you which button you clicked on the command prompt then search that in clickingmost, and Voila!
Hope I helped.
